data.chText: 在英国英语中，staff（第1义）可作单数：
data.enText: In BrE staff (sense 1) can be singular
(= a group of ten people) or plural.
I have ten staff working for me.

data.chText: 该词如果作动词的主语，动词用复数：
data.enText: If it is the subject of a verb, this verb is plural.

data.chText: 这家店的员工非常乐意帮忙。
data.enText: The staff in this shop are very helpful.

data.chText: 在北美英语中，staff（第1及第2义）只能作单数：
data.enText: In NAmE staff (senses 1 and 2) can only be singular.

data.chText: 职工十人（但不能用ten staff）
这家店的员工非常乐意帮忙。
data.enText: The staff in this store is very helpful.

data.chText: 复数形式staffs较少用，但在英国英语和北美英语中均指两批或以上的职员：
data.enText: The plural form staffs is less frequent but is used in both BrE and NAmE to refer to more than one group of people.

means: (大、中、小学的)管理人员，行政人员

tr: a strong rod or stick with a specialized utilitarian purpose
example: he walked with the help of a wooden staff

tr: (music) the system of five horizontal lines on which the musical notes are written
a rod carried as a symbol
the body of teachers and administrators at a school
example: the dean addressed the letter to the entire staff of the university

tr: personnel who assist their superior in carrying out an assigned task
example: the hospital has an excellent nursing staff
the general relied on his staff to make routine decisions

tr: building material consisting of plaster and hair
used to cover external surfaces of temporary structure (as at an exposition) or for decoration

example: This position is not always staffed
The two men staff the reception desk

value.def: The staff of an organization are the people who work for it.

example.ex: The outpatient program has a staff of six people...
example.tran: 门诊部有 6 名工作人员。

example.ex: Many employers seek diversity in their staffs.
example.tran: 很多雇主寻求雇员的多样性。

value.tran: (一组织的)全体工作人员，全体，职员

value.def: People who are part of a particular staff are often referred to as staff .

example.ex: 10 staff were allocated to the task...
example.tran: 10名员工被分配来完成这项任务。

example.ex: He had the complete support of hospital staff.
example.tran: 他得到了医院职工的全力支持。

value.tran: (全体工作人员中的)部分成员

value.def: If an organization is staffed by particular people, they are the people who work for it.

example.tran: 它们的工作人员都是志愿者。

example.ex: The center is staffed with highly trained physicians...
example.tran: 该中心配备了训练有素的医生。

example.ex: The centre is staffed at all times...
example.tran: 该中心随时都有工作人员。

example.ex: Some have regular clinics staffed by nursing officers.
example.tran: 一些设有配备护理军官的常规诊所。

value.tran: 由…担任工作人员;由…供职

example.ex: The house allocated to them was pleasant and spacious, and well-staffed.
example.tran: 分配给他们的房子舒适宽敞，并配齐了工作人员。

value.def: A staff is a strong stick or pole.
A staff is the five lines that music is written on.
